# 📢 Noise Pollution Monitoring System for Schools and Hospital Zones

## 📌 Abstract

The *Noise Pollution Monitoring System for Schools and Hospital Zones* is an embedded system designed to monitor and control environmental noise levels in sensitive areas. Excessive noise in schools affects students' concentration and learning, while in hospitals it can disturb patients and delay recovery.

This system uses a noise sensor and a microcontroller (Arduino) to continuously monitor sound levels and display them on an LCD. When the noise exceeds a predefined threshold, an alert (LED/Buzzer) is triggered. The system is cost-effective, easy to use, and suitable for real-time applications.

---

## 📖 Introduction

Noise pollution is a major environmental issue caused by urbanization, traffic, and human activities. Sensitive areas like schools and hospitals require strict noise control to maintain productivity and health.

Traditional methods like signboards are ineffective. This project introduces an automated solution using embedded systems to continuously monitor noise and provide instant alerts. The system improves discipline, awareness, and environmental quality.

